ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: You gotta do what you gotta do.

This is good class to build on the theoretical foundations started in ECON550 and learn asymptotic techniques. It does not necessarily cover practical techniques so another course may be helpful on this front.
Well, you have to take it, sorry.
I would strongly recommend it in order to grasp some advance econometric concept.
Basic theory of advance econometrics, so it is a must for anyone doing empirical research.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Provides foundations for the development of, and derivation of characteristics of, semiparametric estimators.
It taught me asymptotic techniques which are going to be useful for my research but did not get a lot of practical skills which would have been even more helpful.

I learned a lot, but we spent a lot of time at the beginning going over thing we had learned in Don's class, and could have skipped. I think it would have been better with a more clear syllabus of what we were supposed to cover.
I learned a lot during this course and the applied tools we covered will be useful in my future.
